					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.g400.co.uk/cantabits/archives/630#comment-76&quot;&gt;Alastair&lt;/a&gt;.

What I was alluding to, but didn&#039;t have enough characters in the tweet to explain, was that the operating system seems to imply a lot of a device&#039;s aesthetics beyond those related to functionality. The Windows Phone 8 designs are perhaps the most explainable, with the phones mimicking the brightly coloured rectangles (it is somewhat disappointing to see such convergence). However, why the leading Android devices are white with straight sides, similar convex rear designs, curved tops and bottoms, three buttons below the screens and horizontally centred but vertically high main cameras (amongst other similarities), is less clear. The iPhones fit the pattern too though, as you rightly point out, that&#039;s primarily for different reasons. However, it is notable that Apple didn&#039;t have to make the iPad and iPod Touch as similar to the iPhone as they are.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://www.g400.co.uk/cantabits/archives/630#comment-76">Alastair</a>.</p>
<p>What I was alluding to, but didn&#8217;t have enough characters in the tweet to explain, was that the operating system seems to imply a lot of a device&#8217;s aesthetics beyond those related to functionality. The Windows Phone 8 designs are perhaps the most explainable, with the phones mimicking the brightly coloured rectangles (it is somewhat disappointing to see such convergence). However, why the leading Android devices are white with straight sides, similar convex rear designs, curved tops and bottoms, three buttons below the screens and horizontally centred but vertically high main cameras (amongst other similarities), is less clear. The iPhones fit the pattern too though, as you rightly point out, that&#8217;s primarily for different reasons. However, it is notable that Apple didn&#8217;t have to make the iPad and iPod Touch as similar to the iPhone as they are.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
