					<description><![CDATA[There are some similarities but that&#039;s what design is about isn&#039;t it? Eventually it evolves into the accepted norm which most people are happy with and unpopular designs are forgotten about. The last example isn&#039;t really a surprise! Both made by Apple, not really a redesign at all, just new insides and software really... But then why would they bother redesigning something that works and sells in the millions?

For an example going back further in time look at Porsche hardly changed (in looks) since it started - still going strong!]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There are some similarities but that&#8217;s what design is about isn&#8217;t it? Eventually it evolves into the accepted norm which most people are happy with and unpopular designs are forgotten about. The last example isn&#8217;t really a surprise! Both made by Apple, not really a redesign at all, just new insides and software really&#8230; But then why would they bother redesigning something that works and sells in the millions?</p>
<p>For an example going back further in time look at Porsche hardly changed (in looks) since it started &#8211; still going strong!</p>
